headline: The Biggest Retailers Are Thriving in the Tariff Economy
summary: In the tariff economy, retailers who cater to cautious consumers are winning.  Walmart Amazon  and the owner of T.J. Maxx are scooping up market share from rivals by offering shoppers good deals and convenience.  In a bid to ease the burden on stressed-out consumers and undercut competitors, Walmart has kept price increases to a minimum by absorbing much of the tariff cost.
